# Nebulaos — PRD

### v0.1 MVP

-----

## 1. The problem

ADHD creative brains don’t struggle with ideas. They struggle with the avoided thing sitting in the corner of every tab, every morning, every week. The copy that needs writing. The spec that needs finishing. The task with no clear edges that feels too big to start and too vague to finish.

That’s Nebulaos: nebulous chaos. The enemy.

The fix isn’t another productivity app. It’s presence. A thinking partner sitting next to you who keeps you company, notices when you’ve wandered off, and helps you find your way back. No judgment. No taking over. Just someone who’s there.

**Success looks like this:**

- Task gets done in the session
- Output is ready for feedback, no sloppy mistakes, no gold-plating
- The hour felt productive, not punishing
- You’d open it again for the next avoided thing
- Time on task is measurably higher than going it alone

-----

## 2. Who it’s for

One person right now. An ADHD creative who:

- Goes time-blind. An hour disappears and they can’t account for it.
- Avoids discomfort. When something feels hard or fuzzy, dopamine wins. Twitter opens. Slack gets checked.
- Runs 3 things at once mentally. Committing to one thing feels like losing the other 2.
- Does better when someone else is in the room. The body-double effect is real.
- Hates being managed. Shame makes it worse. Warmth makes it better.

The session outcome they’re after:

> “The thing I was putting off is done. No sloppy mistakes. Ready for feedback. Scope felt manageable because I just started and kept going.”

-----

## 3. What Nebulaos does (and doesn’t do)

Nebulaos listens, watches, and talks. That’s it.

It can’t edit your doc. Can’t open apps. Can’t search the web for you. Read-only access to context, zero agency over your work.

Think of it like a colleague sitting next to you. They see your screen. They hear you thinking aloud. They notice when you’ve been on the wrong tab for 10 minutes. They ask “still on the copy?” They don’t fix it for you.

**Non-goals for MVP:**

- No editing, opening, or acting on any file or app
- No raw audio stored past the current session
- No cloud required (cloud LLM is fallback only)
- No teams, shared sessions, or multi-user anything
- No integrations with calendars, task managers, or project tools
- macOS only
- No model fine-tuning (learning happens via RAG and post-session reflection)
- No GUI. Terminal first. UI comes later when the core loop is proven.

