## 4. User stories

### Story 1 — Starting a session

*As an ADHD creative, I want to tell Nebulaos what I’m working on verbally so it understands the goal before we start.*

- Session starts with voice, no form filling
- Nebulaos confirms it understood and asks at most 2 follow-up questions
- User names relevant workspaces verbally (“this Figma, this doc”)
- RAG context loads silently in the background
- We’re going within 3 minutes of opening the terminal

### Story 2 — Thinking out loud

*As an ADHD creative, I want to think aloud and have Nebulaos respond naturally so the task feels less lonely.*

- Nebulaos listens the whole time, responds when it’s actually useful
- Silence is fine. Nebulaos doesn’t fill it.
- Conversational tone, not assistant tone
- Picks up on half-finished thoughts and frustration without needing a formal question
- Never touches your work

### Story 3 — Catching drift

*As an ADHD creative, I want Nebulaos to notice when I’ve wandered off so I don’t lose 20 minutes without realising.*

- Screenshot on every app/tab focus change, plus every 5 minutes as a heartbeat
- Off-workspace activity gets a soft verbal check-in, not an alarm
- Phrased like curiosity: “still on the copy?” not “you’re off task”
- User explains, Nebulaos accepts. “Checking a reference” closes it.
- Typing slowdown combined with off-workspace = higher confidence drift signal

### Story 4 — Time awareness

*As someone who goes time-blind, I want a visible indicator of session progress so I always know roughly where I am.*

- Progress bar in terminal (via `indicatif` crate)
- Bar drains on off-task time, not a fixed clock
- No alarm when it empties. Soft verbal note only.

### Story 5 — Getting better over time

*As a returning user, I want Nebulaos to remember how I work so it gets more useful session by session.*

- After each session, Nebulaos writes a structured reflection to local store
- Captures: workflow patterns, where I got stuck, what kind of nudge actually worked
- Next session on the same project type pulls that context automatically
- I can see and delete anything stored

### Story 6 — Session log and export

*As a solo user, I want to export my session log so I can drop it into Claude or ChatGPT and spot my own patterns.*

- Log written locally at session end
- Contains: goal declared, time on/off task, drift events, conversation summary, completion status
- One export command, clean text output
- No raw audio or screenshots in the log
- Post-MVP: send report to an accountability partner via email/iMessage, user approves before it goes

### Story 7 — Switching tasks mid-session

*As an ADHD creative who gets interrupted, I want Nebulaos to help me park cleanly so nothing gets lost when I have to switch.*

- User says “I need to deal with something else”
- Nebulaos asks: “where are you with this — good place to stop or need a few more minutes?”
- Current task logged as paused with a context snapshot
- New task gets a fresh session declaration
- Paused task stays visible. User decides when to come back. Nebulaos doesn’t auto-resume.

### Story 8 — Staying on topic

*As someone who will absolutely go off on tangents, I want Nebulaos to pull me back when the conversation drifts.*

- Off-topic conversation treated the same as screen drift
- One warm redirect: “that’s interesting, but we’re on the copy — where were you?”
- Logged as a drift event if it keeps going
- Nebulaos never starts off-topic conversations itself

