## 5. AI and models

### Stack

|Role                         |Model                                    |Where                                      |
|-----------------------------|-----------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
|Speech to text               |Whisper Tiny                             |On-device                                  |
|Text to speech               |Kokoro                                   |On-device                                  |
|Vision / attention classifier|Candle (HuggingFace Rust)                |On-device                                  |
|Thinking partner             |Hermes 2 Pro 7B or Hermes 3 8B via Ollama|On-device (~4-5GB RAM, fine on M1 16GB)    |
|Heavy reasoning fallback     |Claude API                               |Cloud (text summaries only, no screenshots)|

### Memory

|Store      |What’s in it                                     |Who updates it                  |
|-----------|-------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------|
|Project RAG|Transcripts, briefs, copy, docs                  |User ingests manually           |
|User model |Workflow patterns, stuck points, what nudges work|Hermes writes after each session|

### How it should behave

- **Restraint.** Knows when to stay quiet. Silence is a valid output.
- **Warmth.** Conversational, not clinical. Never sycophantic.
- **Awareness.** Builds a picture of the current task from screen context and RAG, not just what the user says out loud.
- **No hands.** Read-only. Always.

### Evaluation (MVP)

- Did the user finish what they declared? (binary)
- Time on task vs off task ratio from the session log
- Would they open it again? (self-report)
- Test: 1hr website copy session, with and without Nebulaos

