## 6. Technical spec

### Stack

```
Rust CLI (terminal, no GUI for MVP)
├── Whisper Tiny — STT via Rust bindings
├── Kokoro — TTS via ONNX runtime
├── Candle — vision classifier for screenshots
├── Ollama HTTP client — Hermes 2 Pro 7B / 3 8B
├── LanceDB — embedded vector store, no separate process
├── indicatif — terminal progress bar
└── Claude API — cloud fallback, text only
```

### Architecture

```
Mic → Whisper (STT) ──────────────────────────────┐
Screen capture → Vision classifier → Session log ──→ Hermes (Ollama)
LanceDB (project RAG + user model) ───────────────┘
                                                    ↓
                                          Kokoro (TTS) → Speaker
                                                    ↓
                                     indicatif bar (terminal UI)
                                                    ↓
                               Post-session: structured log → export
```

### Privacy

- Screenshots processed on-device and discarded. Never transmitted.
- Only text summaries reach the cloud LLM. No raw content, no audio.
- Audio cleared after each session.
- LanceDB lives locally. User controls what gets deleted.
- Open source. Privacy is in the architecture, not a policy.

