## 7. Risks and roadmap

### Risks

|Risk                                                         |Likelihood|Mitigation                                   |
|-------------------------------------------------------------|----------|---------------------------------------------|
|On-device model quality not good enough for real conversation|Medium    |Claude API fallback for the hard moments     |
|Continuous STT kills battery or CPU while working            |Medium    |Event-driven capture, not a stream           |
|Kokoro voice sounds robotic, breaks the presence             |Low-Medium|Spend time on voice selection before shipping|
|Vision classifier too blunt for context judgment             |Medium    |Ask first, assume second                     |
|User just ignores it (still escapable)                       |High      |Warmth over time. Report mechanic in v1.1.   |

### Roadmap

**MVP — does it work?**

- 1hr website copy session
- Rust CLI: STT + TTS + screen capture + Hermes + LanceDB + indicatif
- Session log + export
- One question: did the task get done?

**v1.1 — does it feel right?**

- Tune interrupt timing from real session data
- Better drift detection confidence scoring
- Post-session reflection working reliably
- User model building meaningfully over sessions
- Accountability report via email/iMessage

**v2.0 — does it scale?**

- Tauri + Svelte UI (replaces terminal)
- Windows support
- Session history dashboard
- Persona tuning (more/less talkative)
- Possible wider release

